org.jtrim2.taskgraph

Class TaskFactoryKey<R,I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jtrim2.taskgraph.TaskFactoryKey<R,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - the return type of the task nodes created by the defined task node factory
    I - the type of the argument passed to the task node factory when requested for a node to be created

    public final class TaskFactoryKey<R,I>
extends Object
    Defines the key uniquely identifying a particular task node factory. With the task factory argument itself, it also uniquely identifies a particular node in the task execution graph.

    Thread safety

    This class is immutable (with the assumption that the custom key is also immutable, and as such, its methods can be safely accessed from multiple concurrent threads.

    Synchronization transparency

    The methods of this class are synchronization transparent.
    See Also:
    TaskNodeKey, TaskGraphDefConfigurer
